      }
    ],
    "abstractNote": "The texts relating to Bardaisan\u2019s cosmology testify that the world came into existence from the <i>es\u1e6duks\u0113 / \u012bty\u0113</i>, which would correspond to the primordial elements of the Greek philosophical tradition. Although Bardaisan\u2019s cosmology is already studied, the testimonies about the <i>es\u1e6duks\u0113 / \u012bty\u0113</i> contain some contradictions difficult to explain. The present article proposes a new interpretation of Bardaisan\u2019s doctrine, based on the comparison with Aristotle\u2019s cosmology. The Aristotelian approach to the movement of the elements, their qualities and their reciprocal actions gives a better understanding of the obscure points of the Bardaisanite doctrine and makes it possible to recover its coherence. Moreover, the debate engaged by Aristotle with the atomistic theories helps to understand the place of perd\u0113 - atoms - in Bardaisan\u2019s system.",
